cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of collaborative robots in industrial settings and their performance in a mock collaborative task. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on the safety of physical human-robot interaction and the use of sensors and algorithms to track human body parts. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is mentioned in the paper as the authors use an RGB-D sensor and skeleton extraction algorithm for human pose estimation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the authors may have used machine learning techniques in their algorithm for human pose estimation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the use of standards for safe physical human-robot interaction and the implementation of two collaborative regimes in a single application.
